<h1>Ten O'Clock News</h1>
<p class="about"><i>The Ten O'Clock News</i> was a nightly news program produced and broadcast by WGBH.  A local program aimed at the Boston audience, <i>The Ten O'Clock News</i> debuted on January 15, 1976. WGBH Media Library and Archives has preserved and described 523 tapes from <i>The Ten O'Clock News</i>, and its precursors, <i>The Reporters</i> and <i>Evening Compass</i>.  Dating from 1974 to 1991, this collection focuses on news stories relating to Boston's African American community. This project was funded by the <a href="http://www.imls.gov/index.shtm" target="_blank">Institute of Museum and Library Services.</a></p>

